    Summer wind    

27
00:05:01,858 --> 00:05:04,224
    Summer wind    

28
00:05:04,327 --> 00:05:07,353
    Came blowin'in    

29
00:05:07,463 --> 00:05:09,954
    From across the sea    

30
00:05:10,066 --> 00:05:12,500
[ Man ]
Are we expecting
Miss Aubrey this evening?

31
00:05:12,602 --> 00:05:15,093
       [ Continues ]
We are.

32
00:05:15,204 --> 00:05:18,173
What name
am I registered under ?
Mike Nelson.

33
00:05:18,274 --> 00:05:21,971
The Sea Hunt fella,
you know.
All right.

34
00:05:22,078 --> 00:05:25,775
Tell the desk that
I don't wanna talk to anybody
except her, all right?

35
00:05:25,882 --> 00:05:28,851
Mm-hmm.
And, Fitch, tonight,

36
00:05:28,951 --> 00:05:31,647
everything
has to be perfect.

37
00:05:31,754 --> 00:05:33,915
Have I ever let you down,
Mr. Chapel ?

38
00:05:35,024 --> 00:05:38,357
    Two sweethearts    

39
00:05:38,461 --> 00:05:40,827
    And the summer wind    

40
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:46,631
    Like painted kites    

41
00:05:46,736 --> 00:05:52,368
    Those days and nights
They went flying by    

42
00:05:55,278 --> 00:05:57,803
    The world was new    

43
00:05:57,914 --> 00:06:00,280
    Beneath a blue    

44
00:06:00,383 --> 00:06:03,011
    Umbrella sky    

45
00:06:04,687 --> 00:06:08,453
This is Mr. Chapel.
Have there been any messages?

46
00:06:08,558 --> 00:06:10,458
No?

47
00:06:11,761 --> 00:06:13,661
Thanks.

48
00:06:31,347 --> 00:06:33,338
[ Woman On Phone ]
Hi, this is Jane.

49
00:06:33,449 --> 00:06:35,644
Leave me a message
after the beep
and I'll get back to you.

50
00:06:35,751 --> 00:06:37,685
Thanks a lot.
Bye-bye.
[ Beeps ]

51
00:06:37,787 --> 00:06:42,156
jane, it's Billy.
I'm worried now,
so... please call.

52
00:06:45,628 --> 00:06:47,528
Are you there?

53
00:06:55,238 --> 00:06:58,366
[ TV Continues,
lndistinct ]

54
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,060
[ Groans ]

55
00:07:29,338 --> 00:07:32,000
[ knocking On Door ]

56
00:07:36,512 --> 00:07:38,912
[ knocking Continues ]

57
00:07:51,027 --> 00:07:53,928
jesus.
I've been bangin'
out here forever.

58
00:07:56,566 --> 00:07:58,966
What the hell
happened to you?

59
00:08:00,803 --> 00:08:02,703
You weren't at the gym.

60
00:08:04,674 --> 00:08:07,199
Is Jane here?
No.

61
00:08:11,180 --> 00:08:13,080
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, Jesus.

62
00:08:15,284 --> 00:08:18,185
Oh. Hmm.
[ knocking On Door ]

63
00:08:18,287 --> 00:08:20,983
Chap, you know,
a lot of little bottles
makes a big bottle.

64
00:08:21,090 --> 00:08:24,992
Hey. Hey, that could be her.

65
00:08:25,094 --> 00:08:28,552
You gotta throw
today, chief.
Gus, do me a favor, huh?

66
00:08:28,664 --> 00:08:32,395
Get the door !
All right.

67
00:08:32,501 --> 00:08:36,528
Throw some water on your hair.
lt might look like
you took a shower.

68
00:08:38,507 --> 00:08:40,407
[ Door Opens ]

69
00:08:41,911 --> 00:08:43,811
No, not at all.

70
00:08:43,913 --> 00:08:45,813
He's in the bathroom
back there.

71
00:08:50,086 --> 00:08:53,214
Mr. Wheeler.
Good mornin', Billy.
Got a minute?

72
00:08:53,322 --> 00:08:55,222
Yeah, sure.

73
00:08:57,126 --> 00:08:59,356
It's not easy
to get up here.

74
00:09:01,130 --> 00:09:04,031
They treat me right.
They didn't have you
on the register.

75
00:09:04,133 --> 00:09:06,829
I can't remember
all your names.
Price of fame, huh?

76
00:09:09,372 --> 00:09:12,205
Can I--
Can I get you something?
No, no, no, no.

77
00:09:12,308 --> 00:09:14,208
Let's just sit.

78
00:09:15,311 --> 00:09:17,211
Yeah.

79
00:09:17,313 --> 00:09:19,508
lt's been a rough season.

80
00:09:19,615 --> 00:09:22,083
[ Chuckles ]

81
00:09:22,184 --> 00:09:24,675
Yeah.
Always next year.

82
00:09:24,787 --> 00:09:27,449
Not for me.

83
00:09:27,556 --> 00:09:30,787
It's one of those secrets
everybody knows.

84
00:09:30,893 --> 00:09:33,123
What you don't know
is it's offiicial.

85
00:09:34,230 --> 00:09:36,130
Billy, I sold the Tigers.

86
00:09:44,407 --> 00:09:47,103
Well, that's, uh, great.

87
00:09:47,209 --> 00:09:49,541
Is it?

88
00:09:49,645 --> 00:09:51,545
Yeah.

89
00:09:53,282 --> 00:09:59,084
Billy, you've been
the heart and soul
of this team.

90
00:09:59,188 --> 00:10:01,088
Like family.

91
00:10:02,658 --> 00:10:06,424
All the negotiations,
the bastards never said a word.

92
00:10:09,765 --> 00:10:11,665
Said what?

93
00:10:14,003 --> 00:10:16,164
They want to trade you
to the Giants.

94
00:10:27,483 --> 00:10:29,383
Wow.

95
00:10:31,721 --> 00:10:33,916
Is-Is that why
you're here?

96
00:10:34,023 --> 00:10:35,991
No.

97
00:10:36,092 --> 00:10:39,391
I don't know how
to say this.

98
00:10:39,495 --> 00:10:42,123
You know,
I've been watching you
for 18 years.

99
00:10:42,231 --> 00:10:45,223
[ Sighs ]
Nothing--

100
00:10:45,334 --> 00:10:47,996
Nothing has given me
more pleasure.

101
00:10:48,104 --> 00:10:50,004
You're like the old boys.

102
00:10:50,106 --> 00:10:52,506
They were golden.

103
00:10:52,608 --> 00:10:55,577
They had that special pride.

104
00:10:55,678 --> 00:10:57,908
When they were done,
they were done.

105
00:10:58,013 --> 00:11:00,573
Nobody had to show them
the door.

106
00:11:06,622 --> 00:11:08,522
Are you saying
I should retire?

107
00:11:08,624 --> 00:11:12,116
Why not?
It wouldn't hurt
the negotiations,

108
00:11:12,228 --> 00:11:14,753
and it would serve
those sons of bitches right.

109
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:20,461
I, uh--

110
00:11:20,569 --> 00:11:23,936
I don't know.
I don't know what to say.

111
00:11:24,039 --> 00:11:26,974
Well, you know,
you can't tell me
you haven't thought about it.

112
00:11:27,076 --> 00:11:31,376
And you've been smart
with money, right? Right?
Yeah.

113
00:11:36,752 --> 00:11:38,652
I've always been
a Tiger.

114
00:11:38,754 --> 00:11:40,654
I know, son.

115
00:11:42,158 --> 00:11:44,217
That's why
this is killing me.

116
00:11:47,963 --> 00:11:52,093
You know,
my dad bought this team
when I was seven.

117
00:11:52,201 --> 00:11:54,101
I grew up
watching the Tigers.

118
00:11:54,203 --> 00:11:57,366
I was gonna leave
the team to my kids, but
they don't even like baseball.

119
00:11:57,473 --> 00:11:59,839
Everything's changed,
Billy.

120
00:11:59,942 --> 00:12:02,103
The players, the fans,

121
00:12:02,211 --> 00:12:04,372
TV rights, arbitrations.

122
00:12:04,480 --> 00:12:06,380
It isn't the same.
The game stinks.

123
00:12:06,482 --> 00:12:08,780
And I--

124
00:12:08,884 --> 00:12:11,318
I can't be
a part of it anymore.

125
00:12:12,521 --> 00:12:15,581
[ Telephone Ringing ]

126
00:12:15,691 --> 00:12:18,421
[ Ringing Continues ]

127
00:12:18,527 --> 00:12:21,428
[ Sighs ]
Well--

128
00:12:21,530 --> 00:12:24,055
Billy, you want me
to, um--

129
00:12:24,166 --> 00:12:26,066
No.

130
00:12:32,041 --> 00:12:34,100
Hello. Jane !

131
00:12:34,210 --> 00:12:38,237
Where are you?
You're downstairs?

132
00:12:38,347 --> 00:12:40,907
No ! Just stay there,
all right?

133
00:12:41,016 --> 00:12:42,916
just stay where you're at.
I'm on my way down.

134
00:12:43,018 --> 00:12:45,213
[ Hangs Up Phone ]
What do you want me
to tell 'em, Billy?

135
00:12:45,321 --> 00:12:48,688
Look, I--
I need more time, all right?

136
00:12:57,399 --> 00:13:00,493
The game doesn't stink,
Mr. Wheeler.

137
00:13:00,603 --> 00:13:02,503
It's a great game.

138
00:13:05,941 --> 00:13:08,068
Billy, what's up?

139
00:13:11,180 --> 00:13:13,080
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]

140
00:13:13,182 --> 00:13:15,082
I tried to get her
in a cab, Mr. Chapel,

141
00:13:15,184 --> 00:13:18,620
but she said she wanted to--
just go up and walk
up in Central Park.

142
00:13:18,721 --> 00:13:20,621
Go easy on our boys
today, Billy.

143
00:13:42,912 --> 00:13:45,312
Jane?

144
00:13:47,750 --> 00:13:50,651
jane?
Why didn't you wait?

145
00:13:50,753 --> 00:13:52,812
[ Sniffles ]

146
00:13:52,922 --> 00:13:54,947
Are you crying?

147
00:14:00,796 --> 00:14:03,560
[ Sighs ]
What's the matter ?

148
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:07,193
They didn't have any Kleenex
in the hotel bathroom.
[ Sniffles ]

149
00:14:07,303 --> 00:14:09,430
What's going on, Jane?

150
00:14:09,538 --> 00:14:13,770
I've been sitting in the lobby
for the last two hours.

151
00:14:13,876 --> 00:14:15,776
Doing what?

152
00:14:17,179 --> 00:14:19,739
I'm sorry I didn't call
last night, you know.

153
00:14:19,848 --> 00:14:21,907
I could tell that your voice
was worried enough that--

154
00:14:22,017 --> 00:14:26,215
If something's wrong,
just say it, Jane.
I mean, we don't--

155
00:14:26,322 --> 00:14:28,449
We never had to fake it.

156
00:14:31,427 --> 00:14:33,327
I'm leaving.

157
00:14:33,429 --> 00:14:36,227
I'm going to London.

158
00:14:41,003 --> 00:14:42,903
London?

159
00:14:43,005 --> 00:14:46,168
There's a job, a good job.

160
00:14:46,275 --> 00:14:49,802
An editor's position.
And--

161
00:14:49,912 --> 00:14:52,142
I've been trying to fiigure out
a way to tell you,

162
00:14:52,247 --> 00:14:55,580
but everything sounds so--

163
00:14:56,986 --> 00:15:01,423
What can I say?
I mean, tell me what to say.

164
00:15:05,060 --> 00:15:07,085
I can't tell you, Billy.

165
00:15:08,630 --> 00:15:10,962
It's all right.

166
00:15:11,066 --> 00:15:13,864
I knew it.

167
00:15:13,969 --> 00:15:16,062
From the day I fiirst met you
fiive years ago,
What?

168
00:15:16,171 --> 00:15:19,436
I've always known...
you don't need me.
Knew what?

169
00:15:20,776 --> 00:15:24,268
You and the ball
and the diamond,
you're perfect.

170
00:15:24,380 --> 00:15:26,541
A perfectly beautiful thing.

171
00:15:26,648 --> 00:15:29,583
You can win or lose the game
all by yourself.

172
00:15:32,588 --> 00:15:34,488
I'm sorry.

173
00:15:36,258 --> 00:15:38,749
I'm so sorry.

174
00:15:38,861 --> 00:15:42,820
Have dinner tonight
with me, Jane,
after the game.

175
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:48,295
We'll go to Mario's.
I have a 6:00 plane.

176
00:15:50,706 --> 00:15:52,970
They wanted me there
a week ago when you called,

177
00:15:53,075 --> 00:15:55,009
and I wanted to see you.

178
00:15:55,110 --> 00:15:57,010
I wanted to say good-bye.

179
00:15:59,515 --> 00:16:01,415
Good-bye, Billy.

180
00:16:18,600 --> 00:16:21,797
       [ Rock ]

181
00:16:21,904 --> 00:16:31,870
      

182
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:35,381
[ Male Announcer ]
Welcome to New York
and to Yankee Stadium...

183
00:16:35,484 --> 00:16:38,976
on a crisp and glorious
fall afternoon,

184
00:16:39,088 --> 00:16:43,354
where the Yankees try to win
the divisional title
against the Detroit Tigers.

185
00:16:43,459 --> 00:16:46,428
Hi, everybody.
I'm Vin Scully along
with Steve Lyons,

186
00:16:46,528 --> 00:16:49,395
and welcome
to our fiinal telecast
of the regular season.

187
00:16:49,498 --> 00:16:55,368
You can smell the fall.
The World Series is just around
the corner here in New York.

188
00:16:55,471 --> 00:16:57,939
[ Lyons ]
On paper, today's game
seems easy enough, Vin.

189
00:16:58,040 --> 00:17:00,736
First place team
takes an easy game
from the last place team.

190
00:17:00,843 --> 00:17:04,074
But nothing's ever easy.
Mr. Chapel ?

191
00:17:05,848 --> 00:17:08,373
Hey. Ken Strout.

192
00:17:08,484 --> 00:17:10,543
I was your batboy
a long time ago.

193
00:17:10,652 --> 00:17:13,052
My dad was a Tiger.

194
00:17:15,991 --> 00:17:18,858
joe Strout.
I remember.
[ Chuckles ]

195
00:17:18,961 --> 00:17:20,895
How's he doin' ?

196
00:17:20,996 --> 00:17:23,794
Good. He and Ma are livin'
down in Florida now.

197
00:17:23,899 --> 00:17:26,800
He doesn't move around
too easy, though.
He's got bad knees.

198
00:17:26,902 --> 00:17:29,336
You know,
a little arthritis.

199
00:17:29,438 --> 00:17:31,338
What, are you playin' today?

200
00:17:31,440 --> 00:17:33,431
No, I don't think so.
They just called me up.

201
00:17:33,542 --> 00:17:36,375
Good. Well,
good luck to you.
Thanks.

202
00:17:36,478 --> 00:17:40,039
And give your dad my best.
He was a... great player.

203
00:17:40,149 --> 00:17:42,083
Oh, thanks.
I'll tell him.

204
00:17:50,859 --> 00:17:53,054
[ Man On Radio ]
Live from Yankee Stadium
in New York,

205
00:17:53,162 --> 00:17:55,255
it's
New York Yankees baseball !

206
00:17:55,364 --> 00:17:57,958
Today on the next
to last day of the year,

207
00:17:58,066 --> 00:18:00,398
the Yankees have a chance
to clinch the pennant.

208
00:18:00,502 --> 00:18:03,767
To do it, they'll have
to beat Billy Chapel
and the Detroit Tigers.

209
00:18:03,872 --> 00:18:07,205
Excuse me. Excuse me.
Good afternoon, everyone.
lt is a beautiful fall day...

210
00:18:07,309 --> 00:18:11,143
Could you turn that off?
at Yankee Stadium as the Yankees
are set to clinch the pennant.

211
00:18:11,246 --> 00:18:13,146
No.
But standing in their way...

212
00:18:13,248 --> 00:18:16,945
is the great veteran
right-hander of the Tigers,
Billy Chapel.

213
00:18:18,086 --> 00:18:20,111
Does anybody else know?

214
00:18:20,222 --> 00:18:23,282
No. Nobody
knows nothin'.

215
00:18:23,392 --> 00:18:27,658
Not even Perry.
If they knew, that's all
they'd be talkin' about.

216
00:18:31,833 --> 00:18:33,767
Well, what does Jane say?

217
00:18:33,869 --> 00:18:36,963
[ Sighs ]
jane's movin' to London.

218
00:18:37,072 --> 00:18:40,667
Movin'to London?
What the--

219
00:18:40,776 --> 00:18:44,439
- How are you gonna
manage that?
- We're not.

220
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:50,616
Billy...

221
00:18:50,719 --> 00:18:52,619
this ain't your day.

222
00:18:52,721 --> 00:18:54,621
[ Chuckles ]

223
00:18:57,659 --> 00:18:59,559
What are you gonna do?

224
00:19:02,531 --> 00:19:04,431
I don't know.

225
00:19:08,370 --> 00:19:11,237
That's
Wheeler's nephew.

226
00:19:11,340 --> 00:19:15,174
He sent him down
to get your answer.

227
00:19:15,277 --> 00:19:18,678
Guess he's gonna sit
through the whole game
if he has to.

228
00:19:18,780 --> 00:19:20,941
Poor kid.

229
00:19:21,049 --> 00:19:22,949
Doesn't even know
what he's doin' here.

230
00:19:58,820 --> 00:20:00,720
[ Sniffiing ]

231
00:20:02,457 --> 00:20:05,426
just throw the ball
to the glove, son.
just play catch.

232
00:20:15,537 --> 00:20:18,768
Since you're throwin'
bullets, I'm not even
gonna mention the fact...

233
00:20:18,874 --> 00:20:21,308
that you were an hour late,
and I've been standin' here
trying to fiigure out...

234
00:20:21,410 --> 00:20:23,537
who my starting pitcher
would be if you didn't show up.

235
00:20:23,645 --> 00:20:26,079
Have I ever not showed?

236
00:20:27,549 --> 00:20:30,780
I mean, in 19 years
have I ever not showed?

237
00:20:32,454 --> 00:20:35,355
Well, that's true of everyone
till the fiirst time
they don't show.

238
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:39,116
Billy, I had an idea.

239
00:20:39,227 --> 00:20:43,630
I've pretty much made up
my mind, but I wanted
to run it by you fiirst.

240
00:20:43,732 --> 00:20:45,700
l want Jimmy
to catch today.

241
00:20:45,801 --> 00:20:50,534
l know how you feel about Gus,
but he ain't hittin', Billy.
He ain't hit for a while now.

242
00:20:56,578 --> 00:20:59,069
I haven't said anything,
but we need the left-handed bat.

243
00:20:59,181 --> 00:21:01,081
I want Gus.
Yeah, I know,

244
00:21:01,183 --> 00:21:03,708
and I'd love to take
one of these goddamn games.

245
00:21:03,819 --> 00:21:06,652
We're not layin' down.
We're not gonna be
a red carpet to the Series...

246
00:21:06,755 --> 00:21:09,246
for these guys.

247
00:21:09,358 --> 00:21:13,021
Gus catches,
or I don't pitch.

248
00:21:13,128 --> 00:21:15,926
Me and Gus.
Nobody else.

249
00:21:17,733 --> 00:21:19,633
I hope you hear me.

250
00:21:19,735 --> 00:21:21,930
jesus, Billy, you tellin' me
how to run this team?

251
00:21:22,037 --> 00:21:23,937
[ Grunting ]
No.

252
00:21:24,039 --> 00:21:26,906
But today,
it's me and Gus.

253
00:21:27,008 --> 00:21:29,841
l've never asked you
any other time, okay ?

254
00:21:29,945 --> 00:21:31,845
Good.
Glad you agree.

255
00:21:31,947 --> 00:21:34,313
Can't argue about this
right now.
Gotta warm up.

256
00:21:38,754 --> 00:21:41,416
I'm sorry. We have
a bit of a delay.

257
00:21:41,523 --> 00:21:43,957
We're correcting a bit
of a maintenance problem.

258
00:21:44,059 --> 00:21:46,960
So we don't have a bit
of a crash?

259
00:21:47,062 --> 00:21:48,962
Is there someplace
I can stay?
Yes.

260
00:21:49,064 --> 00:21:52,192
The Premiere Lounge
is just down there
on your right.

261
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:54,200
Thanks.

262
00:21:54,302 --> 00:21:56,202
[ Lyons ]
When the sun goes down,
it'll actually be...

263
00:21:56,304 --> 00:21:58,238
an easier time to hit
for both teams.

264
00:21:58,340 --> 00:22:00,365
[ Scully ]
And now, talkin'about
shadows and sunlight,

265
00:22:00,475 --> 00:22:02,841
that might very well sum up
Billy Chapel.

266
00:22:02,944 --> 00:22:05,469
Long has he stood
in the brilliant sunshine...

267
00:22:05,580 --> 00:22:07,707
in his great, 19-year career.

268
00:22:07,816 --> 00:22:11,650
But now, battling back from
an 8 and 11 record this year,

269
00:22:11,753 --> 00:22:15,883
trying to fiight his way
out of the shadows
back into the sunlight.

270
00:22:15,991 --> 00:22:18,653
He'll be facing Mike Robinson,
followed by Jonathan Warble...

271
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,660
and then Sam Tuttle.

272
00:22:20,762 --> 00:22:23,526
Bottom of the fiirst
inning, no score, and
the Yankees coming up.

273
00:22:43,985 --> 00:22:46,044
What's he lookin' at?

274
00:22:48,990 --> 00:22:53,154
He's lookin'...
at the clouds.

275
00:22:53,261 --> 00:22:55,161
You okay, Chap?

276
00:22:56,965 --> 00:22:59,763
Chappie !
You okay?

277
00:23:08,009 --> 00:23:11,945
[ Man On P.A.]
Catching, number 27, Gus Sinski.

278
00:23:12,047 --> 00:23:13,947
Number 27.

279
00:23:14,049 --> 00:23:17,416
At shortstop, number 7,
Jose Garcia.

280
00:23:17,519 --> 00:23:20,113
Trying to take
my hand off?
Sorry.

281
00:23:20,222 --> 00:23:22,713
just let me set for that juice.
Warn me or something.
Pitching, number 14,

282
00:23:22,824 --> 00:23:26,282
Billy Chapel.
I'm gonna throw a little harder
than usual today.

283
00:23:26,394 --> 00:23:28,294
There's your warning.

284
00:23:28,396 --> 00:23:31,092
Chap, don't throw it away
too early.

285
00:23:34,069 --> 00:23:36,401
Today I'm throwin'
hard, Gus.

286
00:23:38,473 --> 00:23:40,634
You and me?
One more time?

287
00:23:42,544 --> 00:23:44,444
Why not?

288
00:23:48,049 --> 00:23:50,779
[ Cheering ]

289
00:23:56,758 --> 00:24:00,592
[ Man ]
Hey, Chapel ! We got you,
Chapel ! You're done !

290
00:24:00,695 --> 00:24:05,428
We're gonna stick a fork
in you, Chapel !
You are finished !

291
00:24:05,534 --> 00:24:09,766
You are complete !
The Tigers are done !
You're done ! You're finished !

292
00:24:09,871 --> 00:24:11,771
Get outta town !

293
00:24:12,908 --> 00:24:15,433
I can always tell
when I'm in New York.

294
00:24:15,544 --> 00:24:17,705
[ Blowing Horn ]
Hey, Chapel !

295
00:24:17,812 --> 00:24:21,145
Yo, Chapel !
You suck !

296
00:24:22,617 --> 00:24:24,585
You stink on ice !

297
00:24:24,686 --> 00:24:27,018
You couldn't pitch a tent !

298
00:24:28,957 --> 00:24:31,926
[ Shouting, Cheering
lntensifies ]

299
00:24:41,202 --> 00:24:43,864
[ Chapel's Voice ]
Clear the mechanism.

300
00:24:43,972 --> 00:24:45,872
[ Shouting, Cheering
Continues, Muted ]

301
00:24:45,974 --> 00:24:50,673
[ No Audio ]

302
00:24:54,082 --> 00:24:55,982
Hello, Mike.

303
00:25:00,755 --> 00:25:04,384
[ Umpire ]
Strike one !

304
00:25:07,028 --> 00:25:08,962
[ Scully On TV ]
So, Chapel working on Robinson.

305
00:25:09,064 --> 00:25:11,498
Bottom of the fiirst inning.
No score.

306
00:25:14,302 --> 00:25:17,169
And there's a little looper
to Jose Garcia.
One away.

307
00:25:18,773 --> 00:25:20,673
Oh, this is--
This is my lucky day.

308
00:25:20,775 --> 00:25:22,834
Hey, how are ya?
How you doin' ?
Fine. How you doin' ?

309
00:25:22,944 --> 00:25:24,844
Uh, the Bud
on the tap is good.

310
00:25:24,946 --> 00:25:26,846
Okay.
Oh, this is
a beautiful day...

311
00:25:26,948 --> 00:25:28,848
for the big ballpark
in the Bronx.

312
00:25:31,620 --> 00:25:34,487
[ Scully Continues ]
He was an All-American
shortstop there,

313
00:25:34,589 --> 00:25:37,387
and he has certainly done
an outstanding job.

314
00:25:37,492 --> 00:25:39,858
Two solid years, and now
a third with the Yankees.

315
00:25:39,961 --> 00:25:41,861
Pretty good breaking ball.
Did get it up...

316
00:25:41,963 --> 00:25:44,864
but got away with it.
Lot of guys would be upset
about missin' their flight--

317
00:25:44,966 --> 00:25:48,094
You know, delay, this and that--
but this works out
beautiful for me.

318
00:25:50,038 --> 00:25:52,563
[ Scully Continues ]
So, Chapel trying
to derail the Yankees,

319
00:25:52,674 --> 00:25:55,199
and the Yankees trying
to end a season...

320
00:25:55,310 --> 00:25:58,177
that has long been finished
by Detroit.

321
00:26:00,849 --> 00:26:02,680
[ Lyons ]
Warble had a game
earlier this season...

322
00:26:02,784 --> 00:26:04,718
where he had five hits,
nine R.B.l.s.

323
00:26:04,819 --> 00:26:06,719
That's a week
for a lot of guys.

324
00:26:06,821 --> 00:26:09,790
I don't know.
They-They pushed this guy up
to pitch this game.

325
00:26:09,891 --> 00:26:14,453
So, basically we clinch today
and I get to see it.
Beautiful.

326
00:26:14,562 --> 00:26:17,087
[ Scully ]
They were 63 and 97.
The Yankees, meanwhile--

327
00:26:17,198 --> 00:26:20,531
Hi. What
can I get for you?
Chivas and water.

328
00:26:20,635 --> 00:26:22,694
[ Bar Patron ]
Okay, here we go.
Everything is--

329
00:26:22,804 --> 00:26:25,466
[ Scully ] Good sinker.
Oh, look at that.
Ah, it's early.

330
00:26:25,573 --> 00:26:28,701
You got, uh,
nuts, chips, somethin' ?

331
00:26:28,810 --> 00:26:31,643
- We got those pretzels.
- I can make do.

332
00:26:31,746 --> 00:26:34,909
Thank you.

333
00:26:35,016 --> 00:26:37,382
[ Scully ]
Good fastball
with some movement on it.

334
00:26:37,485 --> 00:26:41,148
And down goes Warble.
jesus, he swung at that?
This guy, he's got nothin' now.

335
00:26:41,256 --> 00:26:44,384
If I was Boston, I'd be worried.
I'd be, like, what,
are they throwin' the game?

336
00:26:46,494 --> 00:26:48,655
This guy used to be a monster,
to tell you the truth.

337
00:26:48,763 --> 00:26:50,663
When he first came up,
he was unhittable.

338
00:26:50,765 --> 00:26:52,665
Now, he's a junker.

339
00:26:52,767 --> 00:26:55,292
30-30 three years in a row,

340
00:26:55,403 --> 00:26:57,894
and in baseball circles
we all know that there's no love
lost between these two guys.

341
00:26:58,006 --> 00:26:59,906
They don't like
each other too much.

342
00:27:00,008 --> 00:27:01,908
[ Cheering ]

343
00:27:02,010 --> 00:27:06,003
[ Man On P.A.]
At third base,
number 13, Sam Tuttle.

344
00:27:08,049 --> 00:27:09,949
[ Chapel ]
Sam Tuttle.

345
00:27:10,051 --> 00:27:13,646
I can't think of a better reason
not to be a Yankee.

346
00:27:15,423 --> 00:27:17,789
[ Scully ]
Sam Tuttle hit .625.

347
00:27:17,892 --> 00:27:20,417
He went 5 for 8
against Chapel this year.

348
00:27:20,528 --> 00:27:22,428
[ Lyons ]
That would make me
not like a guy.

349
00:27:22,530 --> 00:27:24,930
[ Scully ]
I would think so.

350
00:27:29,337 --> 00:27:32,602
[ Chanting ]
Tuttle ! Tuttle ! Tuttle !

351
00:27:32,707 --> 00:27:35,107
Tuttle ! Tuttle ! Tuttle !

352
00:27:35,210 --> 00:27:38,839
Tuttle ! Tuttle ! Tuttle !

353
00:27:38,947 --> 00:27:41,211
[ Chanting Continues ]

354
00:27:43,885 --> 00:27:46,513
[ Scully ]
Fastball on the inside corner.
Strike one.

355
00:27:46,621 --> 00:27:49,351
Wasn't that inside?

356
00:27:49,457 --> 00:27:52,119
You never do swing
at the fiirst pitch,
do you, Sam?

357
00:27:59,901 --> 00:28:02,131
No, no,
we're off the page now, Gus.

358
00:28:02,237 --> 00:28:05,638
This is between me and ugly.

359
00:28:05,740 --> 00:28:07,640
Straight heat.

360
00:28:07,742 --> 00:28:09,642
That a boy.

361
00:28:11,813 --> 00:28:14,873
- Strike two !
- Aw, that shit's outside.

362
00:28:16,117 --> 00:28:18,642
No wonder nobody
likes you, Tuttle.

363
00:28:18,753 --> 00:28:21,017
Everything's
a goddamn debate.
[ Scully ] Fastball,

364
00:28:21,122 --> 00:28:23,647
and it runs
right on that outside corner.

365
00:28:23,758 --> 00:28:26,386
So 0 and 2 the count
to Sam Tuttle.

366
00:28:26,494 --> 00:28:30,692
I saw that shitty little
Hollywood movie you did.

367
00:28:37,605 --> 00:28:39,573
Ball !
[ Lyons ]
Gus Sinski wanted that one.

368
00:28:39,674 --> 00:28:43,508
So did Chappie.
You see the reaction
on his face.

369
00:28:43,611 --> 00:28:45,738
That's a pretty good pitch
on the outside corner.

370
00:28:45,847 --> 00:28:49,408
Tuttle didn't like the first
two calls, and now he gets
a break on that outside corner.

371
00:28:49,517 --> 00:28:53,715
That's not the kind of pitch
Chapel's gonna like being called
a ball all day long.

372
00:28:58,626 --> 00:29:03,461
Don't crowd me, Sam.
I hate being crowded.

373
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:08,225
No.

374
00:29:08,336 --> 00:29:11,897
So, 1 and 2 the count,
and whoops, Tuttle has really
moved up on the plate.

375
00:29:12,006 --> 00:29:14,873
He's all over the plate
right now.

376
00:29:20,014 --> 00:29:22,710
Now you got the idea.

377
00:29:27,188 --> 00:29:29,418
[ Scully ]
Uh-oh ! Down goes Tuttle.
[ Fans Protesting ]

378
00:29:29,524 --> 00:29:32,425
What a knockdown pitch
that was. There's
a message being delivered.

379
00:29:32,527 --> 00:29:34,757
Yankee Stadium
is like a schoolyard,

380
00:29:34,863 --> 00:29:38,629
and Bill Murdie looks like
a teacher who sees trouble.

381
00:29:38,733 --> 00:29:41,258
You know, they say
in every great athlete...

382
00:29:41,369 --> 00:29:44,065
there's a mean streak,
and Billy Chapel's no different.

383
00:29:44,172 --> 00:29:47,403
[ Scully ]
Bill Murdie goes
from umpire to referee.

384
00:29:47,508 --> 00:29:49,840
[ Lyons ]
Anytime l played
against this guy,

385
00:29:49,944 --> 00:29:53,345
if he felt like
he had his good stuff,
he'd flip you like this.

386
00:29:53,448 --> 00:29:56,008
Throw a ball right
up there over your head
just to let you know that,

387
00:29:56,117 --> 00:29:58,415
''I can throw the ball
anywhere I want today--''

388
00:29:58,519 --> 00:30:00,851
[ Bar Patron ]
You know, l've been
a Yankee fan since 1958.

389
00:30:00,955 --> 00:30:06,120
- I can name a Yankee
for every number.
- Oh, God. Please don't.

390
00:30:06,227 --> 00:30:08,661
Number one:
Billy Martin, Bobby Richardson.

391
00:30:08,763 --> 00:30:12,597
Number two:
Frank ''The Crow'' Crosetti
and Bobby Murcer.

392
00:30:12,700 --> 00:30:15,999
Number three.. the Babe.
Number four.. Gehrig.
Five..DiMaggio.

393
00:30:16,104 --> 00:30:19,301
Six..Steve Boyer, Roy White.
Excuse me.
Would you mind?

394
00:30:22,076 --> 00:30:25,443
You can't smoke in a bar.
What, now you can't talk
in a bar ?

395
00:30:25,546 --> 00:30:27,480
This ain't church, lady.
[ Scoffs ]

396
00:30:27,582 --> 00:30:30,642
[ Scully ]
Tuttle back up to the plate.
[ Umpire ] 2 and 2 !

397
00:30:30,752 --> 00:30:32,879
Same shit,
different day, huh?

398
00:30:32,987 --> 00:30:35,148
I'd throw it at you again,

399
00:30:35,256 --> 00:30:37,156
but I'm afraid
Murdie'd run me.

400
00:30:41,663 --> 00:30:43,563
Strike three !

401
00:30:43,665 --> 00:30:46,259
[ Scully ]
Oh, good breaking ball.
Got him looking.

402
00:30:46,367 --> 00:30:49,495
[ Lyons ] What a great job
of settin'up a hitter.
Let's take another look.

403
00:30:49,604 --> 00:30:53,665
Tuttle looks like a deer
caught in the headlights.
Chapel just jelly-legged him.

404
00:30:53,775 --> 00:30:57,040
[ Scully ]
So at the end of one,
Tigers nothing, Yankees nothing.

405
00:30:57,145 --> 00:31:01,275
All right, here we go now.
Four, fiive, six.
Let's get something started.

406
00:31:01,382 --> 00:31:03,407
jose, attababy.

407
00:31:03,518 --> 00:31:06,180
It's all about
positioning, right?

408
00:31:06,287 --> 00:31:08,187
You gotta wait on this guy,
all right?

409
00:31:08,289 --> 00:31:10,348
Hey, Mike?
Some water ?
[ Man ] Yeah?

410
00:31:10,458 --> 00:31:13,086
Sure thing, Billy.
You all right?

411
00:31:16,698 --> 00:31:18,791
You got it goin' good
out there.

412
00:31:20,101 --> 00:31:22,865
Make sure
you save something.

413
00:31:28,109 --> 00:31:30,304
Birch wants
to play golf tomorrow.

414
00:31:34,349 --> 00:31:37,250
You know,
I played golf with Birch
the day I met Jane.

415
00:31:39,287 --> 00:31:41,187
You doin' all right?

416
00:31:42,790 --> 00:31:45,588
Yeah.

417
00:31:45,693 --> 00:31:48,287
I'm not hearin' 'em
at all out there.

418
00:32:03,077 --> 00:32:06,808
[ Car Stereo ]
    Are you gathering up
the tears    

419
00:32:06,914 --> 00:32:10,008
    Have you had enough of mine    

420
00:32:10,118 --> 00:32:13,952
    Are you reelin'in
the years    

421
00:32:14,055 --> 00:32:16,421
    Stowin'away the time    
[ Yells ]

422
00:32:16,524 --> 00:32:20,221
- Ooh. Hot.
- Stupid piece of crap !

423
00:32:20,328 --> 00:32:23,593
Yeah, that'll fiix it.

424
00:32:23,698 --> 00:32:25,962
       [ Fades ]

425
00:32:26,067 --> 00:32:29,127
[ Sets Parking Brake ]

426
00:32:32,607 --> 00:32:34,507
[ Shuts Engine Off ]

427
00:32:48,189 --> 00:32:50,089
[ Sighs ]

428
00:32:50,191 --> 00:32:52,853
I don't need any help.

429
00:32:55,763 --> 00:32:58,129
I can see that.
I can see you got your car...

430
00:32:58,232 --> 00:33:00,632
kicked completely
into submission.

431
00:33:00,735 --> 00:33:03,260
I mean it.
just go away.

432
00:33:03,371 --> 00:33:08,035
[ Sighs ]
You know, I can always tell
when I'm in New York.

433
00:33:10,445 --> 00:33:12,743
Do you really know
anything about cars?

434
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:22,619
[ Chuckles ]
You want me to have
a look at it?

435
00:33:22,723 --> 00:33:24,623
Okay.
It's not mine.

436
00:33:24,725 --> 00:33:26,625
It's just a trashy rental.

437
00:33:26,727 --> 00:33:28,854
Yeah. Mine too.

438
00:33:34,669 --> 00:33:37,365
Why don't you try the key?
See if we can't get it started.

439
00:33:40,775 --> 00:33:42,675
[ Ignition Cranking ]

440
00:33:42,777 --> 00:33:45,177
[ Chapel ]
Should've paid attention
in auto shop.

441
00:33:45,279 --> 00:33:47,713
Um--

442
00:33:47,815 --> 00:33:51,216
[ lgnition Cranking ]

443
00:33:56,624 --> 00:34:00,060
- [ Engine Starts ]
- [ Laughing ]

444
00:34:00,161 --> 00:34:02,459
What did you do?
Well, I was--

445
00:34:02,563 --> 00:34:05,794
I have no idea.
I-I don't--
[ Chuckles ]

446
00:34:05,900 --> 00:34:10,530
I don't know anything
about cars. I was just
trying to be manly.

447
00:34:10,638 --> 00:34:13,266
Well, that was great.
Thank you.

448
00:34:13,374 --> 00:34:16,002
You saved my day.
Of course I did.

449
00:34:16,110 --> 00:34:19,910
I said I would.
Where are you headed?

450
00:34:20,014 --> 00:34:24,451
I'm not sure.
Bear Mountain, maybe.

451
00:34:24,552 --> 00:34:27,783
I just threw my stuff
in the car and took off.
Had to get out of the city.

452
00:34:27,889 --> 00:34:30,722
How come?
'Cause summer's over
and l missed it.

453
00:34:30,825 --> 00:34:35,728
You know, I work all the time.
Makes me feel old.
I don't know.

454
00:34:40,701 --> 00:34:42,601
Oh.

455
00:34:43,971 --> 00:34:46,303
Well, thanks again.

456
00:34:51,078 --> 00:34:54,514
So, what's the problem?
My problem
seems to be solved.

457
00:34:54,615 --> 00:34:58,517
Oh, no.
Well, wait a sec.
No, the car's fiine.

458
00:34:58,619 --> 00:35:02,953
But listen, honey,
I gave up on four calls haulin'
my ass out to you, okay?

459
00:35:03,057 --> 00:35:06,322
That's 100 bucks to me.
So if there's nothin' wrong
with this car now,

460
00:35:06,427 --> 00:35:09,487
there will be when I bring it
down to the city, okay?
The car's--

461
00:35:09,597 --> 00:35:12,327
- Everything all right?
- [ Man ]
Everything's peaches, mac.

462
00:35:19,240 --> 00:35:21,834
You're--
You're Billy Chapel.

463
00:35:21,943 --> 00:35:24,776
l can't believe it.
lt's a pleasure to meet you.

464
00:35:24,879 --> 00:35:28,940
I can't believe this.
Oh, I'm sorry.

465
00:35:29,050 --> 00:35:31,348
[ Tow Truck Radio Chattering,
lndistinct ]

466
00:35:31,452 --> 00:35:34,182
You know, you are the greatest
freakin' ballplayer out there.

467
00:35:34,288 --> 00:35:36,279
I'm sor-- I'm sorry.
But you really are.

468
00:35:36,390 --> 00:35:40,292
I'm gonna go get that.
You stay right here, okay?

469
00:35:42,063 --> 00:35:43,826
[ Car Door Opens ]
Billy Chapel.

470
00:35:43,931 --> 00:35:46,764
Nice to meet you.
jane Aubrey.

471
00:35:48,970 --> 00:35:51,461
You know, I--
I got this problem.

