01:10:05,936 --> 01:10:07,995
What are you doing
down there?

939
01:10:08,105 --> 01:10:11,541
My foot's been kicking something
down here all night.

940
01:10:11,642 --> 01:10:13,542
What is--
[ Clicks ]

941
01:10:18,549 --> 01:10:21,541
[ Laughs ]
It's not mine.

942
01:10:21,652 --> 01:10:24,985
Oh, you mean it doubles
as a flashlight?
[ Giggling ]

943
01:10:25,088 --> 01:10:28,785
It's really a flashlight.
I wondered why there were
so many batteries in this room.

944
01:10:28,892 --> 01:10:30,792
Shut up !

945
01:10:33,997 --> 01:10:37,091
I'm hungry.
I'm starving.

946
01:10:37,201 --> 01:10:39,101
To the kitchen.

947
01:10:39,203 --> 01:10:42,036
About 20 hours of labor.

948
01:10:42,139 --> 01:10:46,473
Nicky was so freaked out
he didn't even stick around
for my sixth month.

949
01:10:46,577 --> 01:10:50,707
There was this
unbelievable nurse who stayed
double-shift to be with me...

950
01:10:50,814 --> 01:10:55,308
and feed me ice chips
and tell me when to breathe...

951
01:10:55,419 --> 01:10:58,718
and push and scream.

952
01:10:59,823 --> 01:11:03,953
Then fiinally she came out.

953
01:11:04,061 --> 01:11:07,553
They laid her on my stomach
and I could feel
her little heart beat.

954
01:11:07,664 --> 01:11:10,599
I just kept thinking
over and over,

955
01:11:10,701 --> 01:11:12,862
''You and me.

956
01:11:12,970 --> 01:11:15,939
You and me, little girl.''

957
01:11:16,039 --> 01:11:21,204
And then I rigged out
my backpack like those
baby slings they have now.

958
01:11:21,311 --> 01:11:25,748
We walked out of there,
two kids together.

959
01:11:31,488 --> 01:11:33,388
What are you thinking?

960
01:11:37,661 --> 01:11:40,630
That you're heroic
and I admire you.

961
01:11:43,233 --> 01:11:48,728
And you care a lot about me
but you can't afford
to get involved.

962
01:11:48,839 --> 01:11:50,739
Is that what's next?

963
01:11:55,445 --> 01:11:57,345
No.

964
01:11:59,216 --> 01:12:01,616
I was... thinking about
you and Heather.

965
01:12:09,126 --> 01:12:11,026
And me.

966
01:12:14,531 --> 01:12:17,625
I was really
thinking about...

967
01:12:17,734 --> 01:12:21,363
how nice it would be
to spend time together.

968
01:12:32,883 --> 01:12:34,783
Yeah.

969
01:12:34,885 --> 01:12:36,785
[ All Shouting,
Indistinct ]

970
01:13:00,077 --> 01:13:03,103
Oh ! These are great.

971
01:13:03,213 --> 01:13:05,511
We'll use 'em
in Central Park.

972
01:13:05,615 --> 01:13:08,049
No, we can
use 'em out here.

973
01:13:13,390 --> 01:13:16,052
You ever gotten
your heart broken?

974
01:13:16,159 --> 01:13:20,994
Yeah, when we lost
the pennant in '87.

975
01:13:26,003 --> 01:13:28,972
Would you still love me
if I got burned in a fiire?

976
01:13:29,072 --> 01:13:30,972
Oh !
[ Laughs ]

977
01:13:31,074 --> 01:13:36,171
Yes.
If I ran into a tree
and got paralyzed?

978
01:13:38,048 --> 01:13:39,948
[ Scoffs ]

979
01:13:41,218 --> 01:13:43,812
Yes.

980
01:13:43,920 --> 01:13:46,855
What If I were
totally disfiigured,

981
01:13:46,957 --> 01:13:49,118
if my face were
all scraped away,

982
01:13:49,226 --> 01:13:52,491
I had no arms, no legs,
no brain waves...

983
01:13:52,596 --> 01:13:54,996
and I was being kept alive
on a heart-lung machine.

984
01:13:55,098 --> 01:13:56,998
Would you love me?

985
01:13:57,100 --> 01:13:59,159
No.
[ Laughing ]

986
01:13:59,269 --> 01:14:02,705
But we could still
be friends though.

987
01:14:02,806 --> 01:14:04,706
[ Chuckling ]

988
01:14:07,644 --> 01:14:09,703
Do you believe in God?

989
01:14:12,816 --> 01:14:14,716
[ Whispers ]
Yes.

990
01:14:16,053 --> 01:14:18,988
How old do you think you're
gonna be when you die?

991
01:14:24,327 --> 01:14:26,386
Do you like
white meat or dark?

992
01:14:28,832 --> 01:14:30,925
Dark.

993
01:14:31,034 --> 01:14:32,934
Dark?

994
01:14:33,036 --> 01:14:37,132
The dark part's more fatty,
but it's cool
to like that part.

995
01:14:37,240 --> 01:14:40,505
You like it chopped up?

996
01:14:40,610 --> 01:14:43,602
You know how
people dice it
in the chef salad,

997
01:14:43,713 --> 01:14:45,613
or you like it torn?

998
01:14:45,715 --> 01:14:47,808
I personally
like it torn.

999
01:14:47,918 --> 01:14:50,318
Not that you have to
like it how I like it.

1000
01:15:02,766 --> 01:15:04,666
No questions.

1001
01:15:17,314 --> 01:15:19,646
[ Chapel ]
Why you askin'me
all this stuff?

1002
01:15:19,749 --> 01:15:21,808
[ Jane ]
Because l want to know you.

1003
01:15:25,288 --> 01:15:29,657
Breaking ball,
a comeback right at Billy Chapel
to hold onto the line drive.

1004
01:15:29,759 --> 01:15:32,990
- [ Cheering ]
- [ Lyons ] This is one of
those chuck-and-duck pitches.

1005
01:15:33,096 --> 01:15:36,429
When you throw
a ball like that and it
comes back at you that quick,

1006
01:15:36,533 --> 01:15:38,433
it's almost like
the ball catches you.

1007
01:15:38,535 --> 01:15:40,969
[ Scully ]
So far, Chapel is
gettin'away with it.

1008
01:15:41,071 --> 01:15:43,471
[ All Chanting ]
Go, Tigers, go, Tigers.

1009
01:15:43,573 --> 01:15:46,542
Hey, ho, hey, ho.

1010
01:15:47,644 --> 01:15:51,011
[ No Audible Dialogue ]

1011
01:16:11,968 --> 01:16:14,129
[ Scully ]
We have one out here
in the top of the sixth inning.

1012
01:16:14,237 --> 01:16:18,264
No score.
Spellman has allowed two hits.
Chapel has been perfect.

1013
01:16:18,375 --> 01:16:20,843
The batter is
Gus Sinski, 0 for 1 .

1014
01:16:20,944 --> 01:16:24,175
[ Lyons ]
Gus has had a tough year
this year at the plate,

1015
01:16:24,281 --> 01:16:26,579
but they really pay him
for what he does
behind the plate.

1016
01:16:26,683 --> 01:16:30,119
He handles his pitching staff
so well, and any kind of hit
that he gets...

1017
01:16:30,220 --> 01:16:32,450
is a bonus for this club.

1018
01:16:32,556 --> 01:16:35,081
- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- Yes !

1019
01:16:36,993 --> 01:16:42,397
- Simon Louis'a little slow
in coming up with it.
- Get down ! Get down !

1020
01:16:42,499 --> 01:16:45,229
Safe !
It wasn't close !

1021
01:16:45,335 --> 01:16:47,735
He beat the play !

1022
01:16:47,837 --> 01:16:49,737
Good call.

1023
01:16:53,343 --> 01:16:55,243
Attaboy !

1024
01:16:58,215 --> 01:17:01,776
ln a game like this,
that could be a huge play.

1025
01:17:01,885 --> 01:17:06,481
The last leg double
Sinski had was during
the Reagan administration.

1026
01:17:06,590 --> 01:17:09,582
The Yankees
are now on the phone
talking to the bullpen...

1027
01:17:09,693 --> 01:17:12,025
and they get
a left-hander up.

1028
01:17:12,128 --> 01:17:14,528
Bobby Mack is ticked off
with the Yankees,

1029
01:17:14,631 --> 01:17:19,125
and he gives batter Jose Garcia
the intentional walk.

1030
01:17:19,236 --> 01:17:23,969
ln a moment there'll be runners
at first and second, one out
in the sixth, no score...

1031
01:17:24,074 --> 01:17:28,067
and a left-handed hitter
coming up-- that would be
Brian Whitt.

1032
01:17:35,185 --> 01:17:37,085
[ Whirring ]

1033
01:18:05,282 --> 01:18:07,546
[ Chapel ]
Jane.

1034
01:18:07,651 --> 01:18:10,381
I was just
lookin' for you.

1035
01:18:10,487 --> 01:18:12,387
Billy?

1036
01:18:13,523 --> 01:18:15,423
Oh, my God.

1037
01:18:18,395 --> 01:18:20,886
Can't feel
anything.

1038
01:18:20,997 --> 01:18:25,491
Hold this. Close your
fiingers around it.
Hold it up. Hold it up.

1039
01:18:28,505 --> 01:18:32,066
[ Tires Screech ]

1040
01:18:34,444 --> 01:18:37,311
Hold on, Billy.

1041
01:18:42,319 --> 01:18:45,618
- [ Woman ] Occupation?
- Pitcher. He's hurt his hand.

1042
01:18:45,722 --> 01:18:47,917
- We need a doctor.
- Are you his wife?

1043
01:18:48,024 --> 01:18:50,185
No. No.
Are you a relative?

1044
01:18:50,293 --> 01:18:53,490
Then I'll have to ask you
to wait outside.

1045
01:18:53,596 --> 01:18:55,496
jane.

1046
01:18:55,598 --> 01:18:58,761
My friend cut his hand.
It's bleeding very deeply.

1047
01:18:58,868 --> 01:19:01,359
- Ma'am.
- Please, we need help.

1048
01:19:03,907 --> 01:19:06,899
Is this not America?

1049
01:19:07,010 --> 01:19:10,878
Is baseball not America's
favorite pastime?

1050
01:19:12,282 --> 01:19:15,012
- Can I help you?
- Are you a doctor ?

1051
01:19:15,118 --> 01:19:18,918
- Yes.
- Thank you, God.

1052
01:19:23,326 --> 01:19:25,851
jane.
l'm right here.

1053
01:19:25,962 --> 01:19:28,522
-Jane, call Mike Udall.
- What?

1054
01:19:28,631 --> 01:19:32,328
The trainer in Detroit.
Call him.
Tell him what happened.

1055
01:19:32,435 --> 01:19:36,235
I'm going with you.
Sorry, there's not enough
room in the Medivac.

1056
01:19:36,339 --> 01:19:39,137
You're gonna need
to stay here.

1057
01:19:45,048 --> 01:19:46,982
jane !

1058
01:19:49,586 --> 01:19:52,749
Call Mike.
He's the most important person
for me right now.

1059
01:19:59,262 --> 01:20:01,321
You need to clear out.

1060
01:20:27,957 --> 01:20:31,256
-[ Bat Cracks ]
-[ Scully ] There's a little
flare just by Howell's glove...

1061
01:20:31,361 --> 01:20:33,352
- into right field.
- [ Players Shouting,
lndistinct ]

1062
01:20:33,463 --> 01:20:36,796
Here comes Sinski.
Colborn waves him to the plate.

1063
01:20:36,900 --> 01:20:40,028
- The throw.
He is... in there !
- Safe ! Safe !

1064
01:20:40,136 --> 01:20:42,627
- [ Groans ]
- The Tigers take
a 1-to-nothing lead.

1065
01:20:42,739 --> 01:20:46,971
[ Lyons ] What a great slide
by Sinski, sliding away from
the play at the plate.

1066
01:20:47,076 --> 01:20:50,011
Jim Colborn,
the third base coach,
didn't even hesitate.

1067
01:20:50,113 --> 01:20:52,946
Your catcher,
the slowest guy on your team,
comin'around third,

1068
01:20:53,049 --> 01:20:57,850
trying to score in a scoreless
ball game, had no hesitation
at all, sent him all the way--

1069
01:20:57,954 --> 01:21:00,320
[ Continues, lndistinct ]

1070
01:21:00,423 --> 01:21:02,789
[ Man ]
lt's all bullshit, Billy.
Don't listen to it.

1071
01:21:02,892 --> 01:21:07,192
You've done it all.
You've won every award
there is to win.

1072
01:21:07,297 --> 01:21:09,925
You got a room reserved
at Cooperstown, Billy.

1073
01:21:10,033 --> 01:21:13,127
l just don't know how much more
you have to prove.

1074
01:21:13,236 --> 01:21:18,970
Even if you do come back, you're
not gonna be a hundred percent.
You may not even be fifty.

1075
01:21:19,075 --> 01:21:22,909
- [ Chapel ] What'd you say ?
- Nothin'. Let's knock off
for the day. Jane's here.

1076
01:21:23,012 --> 01:21:25,071
What'd you say?
I didn't say anything.

1077
01:21:25,181 --> 01:21:27,274
You said ''if.''
I didn't mean ''if.''

1078
01:21:27,383 --> 01:21:29,749
But you said ''if.''
I only meant--

1079
01:21:29,853 --> 01:21:32,720
Think I'm not
comin' back?
Billy.

1080
01:21:32,822 --> 01:21:35,552
Say it.
You're tired.
Let's quit.

1081
01:21:35,658 --> 01:21:38,821
Say it, chickenshit.

1082
01:21:38,928 --> 01:21:43,524
You got a job.
That's to get me strong
and get me back.

1083
01:21:43,633 --> 01:21:46,067
All right?
You get me back...

1084
01:21:46,169 --> 01:21:48,603
I'll fiigure out how to win.

1085
01:21:52,775 --> 01:21:56,575
You wanna work with me tomorrow,
then get your mind right.

1086
01:21:56,679 --> 01:21:59,273
You get it right,
or you don't come around me.

1087
01:21:59,382 --> 01:22:01,373
[ Jane ]
You mad at me or at Mike?

1088
01:22:01,484 --> 01:22:03,475
[ Chapel ]
Why would I be mad at Mike?

1089
01:22:03,586 --> 01:22:05,986
You practically
tore his head off.
Talk to me.

1090
01:22:06,089 --> 01:22:08,319
Talk?
You don't want to talk.

1091
01:22:08,424 --> 01:22:12,986
You just want to give me
your version of
why I should quit.

1092
01:22:13,096 --> 01:22:15,963
- I want this shit outta here.
- What're you tryin' to do?

1093
01:22:19,836 --> 01:22:23,602
Are you trying to make me mad?
Are you gonna pack up my things
and make me go...

1094
01:22:23,706 --> 01:22:26,140
so you can sit here in the dark
and feel sorry for yourself?

1095
01:22:26,242 --> 01:22:30,576
Well, forget it, Billy.
You can't cook,
you can't drive--

1096
01:22:36,719 --> 01:22:39,051
I'll hire somebody
to drive me.

1097
01:22:41,291 --> 01:22:45,853
Someone who doesn't talk?
Doesn't think bad thoughts?

1098
01:22:45,962 --> 01:22:50,331
Billy, we are gonna
get through this.
You just have to try--

1099
01:22:50,433 --> 01:22:53,061
Try ! Goddamn it,
jane, I'm the only one
who is trying here.

1100
01:22:53,169 --> 01:22:57,606
I got nobody in
the front offiice,
nobody in the press...

1101
01:22:57,707 --> 01:23:00,039
and now I got nobody
in this house...

1102
01:23:00,143 --> 01:23:03,442
that thinks
I'm gonna make it back.

1103
01:23:03,546 --> 01:23:06,014
I have been nothing
but supportive of you.

1104
01:23:06,115 --> 01:23:08,379
I don't want you here,
jane ! I mean--

1105
01:23:09,619 --> 01:23:11,519
Don't you get it?

1106
01:23:14,157 --> 01:23:17,957
You make--
You make me
feel distracted.

1107
01:23:19,929 --> 01:23:21,988
You make me feel weak.

1108
01:23:43,653 --> 01:23:47,384
Billy,
you taught me something.

1109
01:23:47,490 --> 01:23:49,617
You taught me
how to believe again,

1110
01:23:49,726 --> 01:23:53,594
how good things can happen
and that they will happen.

1111
01:23:53,696 --> 01:23:57,257
But now you need to let me
teach you something about
what I know--

1112
01:23:57,367 --> 01:24:01,303
about how sometimes
life seems like it's
slamming you down,

1113
01:24:01,404 --> 01:24:04,999
but it's really
giving you a gift.

1114
01:24:05,108 --> 01:24:08,236
I had a baby
when I was 16.

1115
01:24:08,344 --> 01:24:10,812
That could've
wrecked me.

1116
01:24:10,913 --> 01:24:15,612
But it didn't. Instead,
it was the best thing
that ever happened to me.

1117
01:24:18,454 --> 01:24:22,185
You mean if
life gives you lemons,
you make lemonade?

1118
01:24:24,661 --> 01:24:28,859
- You are such an asshole.
- If you're tellin' me I'm never
gonna hold that ball again--

1119
01:24:33,903 --> 01:24:35,803
I can't.

1120
01:24:37,073 --> 01:24:39,371
Haven't you ever loved
anything that much?

1121
01:24:45,715 --> 01:24:50,084
I'll call the airlines.
See what kind of flights
I can make.

1122
01:24:53,489 --> 01:24:55,389
You do that.

1123
01:24:55,491 --> 01:24:57,391
[ Crowd Cheering ]

1124
01:24:57,493 --> 01:24:59,393
[ lndistinct Chanting ]

1125
01:25:05,468 --> 01:25:07,368
[ Grunts ]

1126
01:25:07,470 --> 01:25:10,871
- Strike !
- [ Scully ] Uh-oh.

1127
01:25:10,973 --> 01:25:13,703
Something happen
to Chapel ?

1128
01:25:13,810 --> 01:25:18,577
Frank Perry is on the steps
of the dugout and apparently
didn't like what he saw.

1129
01:25:18,681 --> 01:25:21,616
Gimme the ball.

1130
01:25:21,718 --> 01:25:24,278
What are you lookin'--
Gimme the ball.

1131
01:25:25,822 --> 01:25:28,416
just stay there.

1132
01:25:28,524 --> 01:25:31,049
[ Crowd Cheering,
Whistling ]

1133
01:25:31,160 --> 01:25:35,062
[ Lyons ] There's something
wrong with either his arm,
his elbow or his shoulder there.

1134
01:25:35,164 --> 01:25:37,962
He doesn't look
very comfortable.

1135
01:25:38,067 --> 01:25:41,503
- Bill, he's hurt.
- [ Scully ] Here he comes.
He's goin'out to visit.

1136
01:25:41,604 --> 01:25:43,663
[ Booing ]

